{"questionId":"25982","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>A scientist conducted a nine-week experiment on two plants, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math>, of the same species.&nbsp;He wanted to determine the effect of using a new plant fertilizer. Plant <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> was given fertilizer&nbsp;regularly, while Plant <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math> was not.</p>\n<p>The scientist found that the height of Plant <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mtext>cm</mtext></math>, at time <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> weeks can be modelled by the&nbsp;function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mi>sin</mi><mo>(</mo><mn>2</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>+</mo><mn>9</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>27</mn></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>9</mn></math>.</p>\n<p>The scientist found that the height of Plant <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mtext>cm</mtext></math>, at time <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi></math> weeks can be modelled by the function <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mo>(</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>32</mn></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mn>0</mn><mo>≤</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>≤</mo><mn>9</mn></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>For <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>6</mn></math>, prove that Plant <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> was always taller than Plant <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>+</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>EITHER</strong></p>\n<p>for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>5</mn><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>and as&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>≥</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>⇒</mo><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>OR</strong></p>\n<p>the minimum value of&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>sin</mi><mfenced><mrow><mn>2</mn><mi>t</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>6</mn></mrow></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>1</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>R1</strong></em></p>\n<p>so for&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>,</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>A</mi></msub><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced><mo>-</mo><msub><mi>h</mi><mi>B</mi></msub><mfenced><mi>t</mi></mfenced><mo>=</mo><mi>t</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>6</mn><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p><br><strong>THEN</strong></p>\n<p>hence for <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>t</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mn>6</mn></math>, Plant <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>A</mi></math> was always taller than Plant <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>B</mi></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>AG</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[3 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"25982","referenceCode":"22M.2.AHL.TZ2.10c","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"For t>6, prove that Plant A was always taller than Plant B.","paper":"2","level":"HL","questionNumber":"c","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 3]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 2—Functions","Topic 2—Functions","AHL 2.15—Solutions of inequalities"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":2}